                            <comment id="15133359" author="maedhroz" created="Thu, 4 Feb 2016 23:53:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15134793" author="jasobrown" created="Fri, 5 Feb 2016 19:28:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=aweisberg&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;aweisberg&quot;&gt;aweisberg&lt;/a&gt; does adding &lt;tt&gt;volatile&lt;/tt&gt; have an affect on publication when changes internal to &lt;tt&gt;scheduledGossipTask&lt;/tt&gt; occur, or only when the &lt;tt&gt;scheduledGossipTask&lt;/tt&gt; variable itself is updated? In &lt;tt&gt;Gossiper#stop&lt;/tt&gt;, we call &lt;tt&gt;scheduledGossipTask.cancel(false);&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Either way, we need the &lt;tt&gt;volatile&lt;/tt&gt; when (re-)starting Gossip (&lt;tt&gt;Gossiper#start()&lt;/tt&gt;), but I&apos;m not sure we solve the problem on stopping gossip as that needs to reference a field internal to the the &lt;tt&gt;ScheduledFuture&lt;/tt&gt; implementation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15134808" author="aweisberg" created="Fri, 5 Feb 2016 19:34:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Adding &lt;tt&gt;volatile&lt;/tt&gt; won&apos;t impact stores to fields in &lt;tt&gt;ScheduledFuture.cancel{false)&lt;/tt&gt;, but ScheduledFuture is thread safe and should ensure publication of the cancellation as well as a happens before relationship with code following cancellation.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="15135082" author="jasobrown" created="Fri, 5 Feb 2016 21:48:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=aweisberg&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;aweisberg&quot;&gt;aweisberg&lt;/a&gt; OK, makes sense. I&apos;ll go ahead and commit, then.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
